Goldman Sachs Plans to Cut Bonuses to Zero, Sunday Times Says

-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   A i r l i e
-- 
2011-10-02T08:08:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-02/goldman-sachs-plans-to-cut-bonuses-to-zero-sunday-times-says.html
Goldman Sachs Group Inc. (GS)  may almost
eliminate bonuses as it girds for a third-quarter loss, the
Sunday Times reported, without saying where it got the
information.  The New York-based bank committed to spend no more than 35
to 45 percent of its revenue on staff pay, the least of Wall
Street firms, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Catherine Airlie in London at 
 cairlie@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net  